<HL>
   Marketing Brief -- Reader's Digest Association Inc.
   U.K. Subsidiary to Acquire
   Publishers David &amp; Charles
</HL>
<DATE>
06/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   RDA
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Reader's Digest Association Inc.'s U.K. subsidiary agreed
to acquire David &amp; Charles PLC for $17 million.
   David &amp; Charles publishes a variety of general interest
and reference books; the company also runs a book club
operation. Reader's Digest said that the board of David &amp;
Charles, based in Newton Abbot, England, will recommend that
shareholders accept the proposal. Holders of some 64% of the
ordinary shares of David &amp; Charles have agreed to the
acquisition.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Reader's Digest Association Ltd., London, is one of 16
international subsidiaries of the U.S. parent, based in
Pleasantville, N.Y., which for several years has been
expanding its global publishing holdings. The parent also
directly markets books, magazines and other products by mail.
</TEXT>
